## Extension Guide: Adding Performance Monitoring to New Algorithms

### Step 1: Identify the Algorithm
Determine the algorithm name and verify it exists in `slowModes` dictionary.

### Step 2: Wrap the Execution
Surround the algorithm execution with measurement calls:

```csharp
private void MyNewAlgorithmHandler(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    BeginPerformanceMeasurement("MyAlgorithm");    // START
    ClearCanvas();
    
    // ... your algorithm code ...
    MyDrawingAlgorithm();
    
    pictureBox1.Image = bmp;
    EndPerformanceMeasurement();                   // END
}
```

### Step 3: No Further Changes Needed
The PerformanceMonitor automatically:
- Detects slow/fast mode from `IsSlow("MyAlgorithm")`
- Collects and stores metrics
- Updates the display label

### Full Example: Adding Performance Tracking to an Existing Algorithm

**Before:**
```csharp
private void button5_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    ClearCanvas();
    // ... drawing code ...
    pictureBox1.Image = bmp;
}
```

**After:**
```csharp
private void button5_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    BeginPerformanceMeasurement("Line_SimpleSlope");  // ADD THIS
    ClearCanvas();
    // ... drawing code (unchanged) ...
    pictureBox1.Image = bmp;
    EndPerformanceMeasurement();                      // ADD THIS
}
```

