## Usage Scenarios

### Scenario 1: Comparing Algorithm Efficiency
1. Run an algorithm with Toggle OFF (Fast mode) - record baseline
2. Run the same algorithm with Toggle ON (Slow mode) - compare overhead
3. Review the SLOW vs FAST comparison in the metrics display
4. Identify computational bottlenecks (high CPU%, high time ratio)

### Scenario 2: Measuring Rendering Performance Degradation
- The system quantifies the "cost" of step-by-step visualization
- High ratio (e.g., 50x slower) = algorithm has many steps
- This helps assess whether slow-motion is practical for real-time education

### Scenario 3: Batch Performance Analysis
- Run multiple algorithms and collect metrics
- Call `PerformanceMonitor.GetSummaryReport()` to analyze all results
- Export report to text file for documentation

### Scenario 4: Baseline Regression Detection
- Record metrics for algorithms in "known good" state
- Re-run after code changes
- Compare new metrics against baselines to detect regressions

