## Summary

The CPU Performance Monitoring System provides a non-invasive, extensible framework for measuring and analyzing the performance of graphics drawing algorithms in both slow-motion educational mode and fast direct-rendering mode. By automatically collecting metrics and computing comparisons, it enables educators and developers to quantify the cost of step-by-step visualization and optimize algorithm implementations.

Integration is straightforward: simply wrap algorithm execution with `BeginPerformanceMeasurement()` and `EndPerformanceMeasurement()`. The system handles all metric collection, storage, comparison, and display automatically.
